{"type":"message","id":"72d97ce9","parentId":"3584bdac","timestamp":"2026-03-07T10:36:55.752Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-03-07 18:36 GMT+8] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: SECURITY AUDIT: Comprehensive OpenClaw security assessment\n\nCONTEXT:\nAudit the entire OpenClaw multi-agent setup for security vulnerabilities, credential exposure, and access control issues.\n\nWHAT TO CHECK:\n\n**1. Credential Security**\n- Check .env files for exposed secrets\n- Verify no API keys in code (should only be in .env)\n- Check for hardcoded passwords\n- Verify Telegram bot tokens are secure\n- Check EmailJS public key vs private key usage\n- Verify RapidAPI keys not exposed\n\n**2. File Permissions**\n- Check .env file permissions (should be 600)\n- Check agent data directories\n- Verify no world-readable sensitive files\n\n**3. Network Security**\n- Check open ports (lsof -i)\n- Verify dashboard authentication (even on localhost)\n- Check gateway security (port 18789)\n\n**4. Access Control**\n- Who can spawn agents?\n- Are there any unauthorized access paths?\n- Check SSH access and keys\n\n**5. Logging & Monitoring**\n- Are credentials logged anywhere?\n- Check log files for sensitive data exposure\n- Review email logs, agent logs\n\n**6. Backup & Recovery**\n- Are credentials backed up securely?\n- Recovery procedures if .env is lost\n\nDELIVERABLE:\n- Security score (0-100)\n- List of critical issues (if any)\n- List of recommendations\n- Priority fixes needed\n\nREPORT BACK WITH:\n- Summary of findings\n- Specific vulnerabilities found\n- Actionable recommendations"}],"timestamp":1772879815748}}
