{"type":"message","id":"ca68ae34","parentId":"970fc1fb","timestamp":"2026-03-07T10:39:07.059Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough information to compile a comprehensive security audit report.\n\nSummary:\n- Security Score: 65/100 (moderate risk)\n- Critical Issues: 3\n- High Issues: 2\n- Medium Issues: 3\n\nLet me compile the final report.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## 🔒 OpenClaw Security Audit Report\n\n### Executive Summary\n**Security Score: 65/100** (Moderate Risk)\n\nThe OpenClaw multi-agent setup has several security strengths but also critical vulnerabilities that require immediate attention.\n\n---\n\n## 🚨 CRITICAL ISSUES (Immediate Action Required)\n\n### 1. **World-Readable Credentials in ARCHIVED Folder**\n- **File**: `/home/darwin/.openclaw/ARCHIVED/aiopsflow-nextjs-full/.env.local`\n- **Permission**: 666 (world-readable)\n- **Exposed Secrets**:\n  - Supabase anon key: `sb_publishable_mI9WLyPuKQVZ4kLd58kovg_KV6slVq2`\n  - Telegram bot token: `8652287514:AAGPP4zXkJR--NPo4nsTMZobqBJZ_prtqf8`\n  - OpenAI API key placeholder (could be real in production)\n- **Risk**: Any user on the system can read these credentials\n- **Fix**: `chmod 600 /home/darwin/.openclaw/ARCHIVED/aiopsflow-nextjs-full/.env.local`\n\n### 2. **Blockchain Private Key Exposed**\n- **Location**: `/home/darwin/.openclaw/.env`\n- **Key**: `POLYCLAW_PRIVATE_KEY=0xe6755a2dfdfe182e6afcf00fbd602c52bd9036cf5749590896094c51622b558b`\n- **Risk**: Full control of blockchain wallet; irreversible if stolen\n- **Status**: File has correct 600 permissions, but key is permanently in .env\n\n### 3. **GitHub Copilot Token in Plain Text**\n- **File**: `/home/darwin/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json`\n- **Token**: `ghu_sB4Z3G9hUTY9svZpwyxBu3rVMwiV2g05IAIM`\n- **Risk**: Unauthorized access to GitHub Copilot API\n- **Status**: File has 600 permissions but token should be env-referenced\n\n---\n\n## ⚠️ HIGH PRIORITY ISSUES\n\n### 4. **Python Tunnel Server on All Interfaces**\n- **Port**: 8081 listening on `0.0.0.0` (all interfaces)\n- **Process**: `/home/darwin/.openclaw/workspace/ai-gateway/tunnel-server/ai_handler.py`\n- **Risk**: Exposed to network; potential unauthorized access\n- **Recommendation**: Bind to `127.0.0.1` only\n\n### 5. **Email Passwords in Plain Text**\n- **Location**: `/home/darwin/.openclaw/workspace/.env`\n- **Exposed**: `HELLO_PASS`, `OPS_PASS`, `SUPPORT_PASS`\n- **Risk**: Email account compromise\n- **Note**: File has correct 600 permissions\n\n---\n\n## 📋 MEDIUM PRIORITY ISSUES\n\n### 6. **Test File with Hardcoded Secrets**\n- **File**: `/home/darwin/.openclaw/workspace/apps/dashboard/server/test-redaction.js`\n- **Contains**: Fake but realistic-looking secrets for testing\n- **Risk**: Could be mistaken for real credentials or used as template\n\n### 7. **Backup Files Present**\n- **Files**: Multiple `.bak` and `.backup` files\n- **Risk**: May contain old credential versions\n- **Recommendation**: Review and secure or delete\n\n### 8. **No .env in .gitignore Verification**\n- **Status**: No .env files found in git history (good!)\n- **Recommendation**: Verify `.gitignore` includes all .env patterns\n\n---\n\n## ✅ SECURITY STRENGTHS\n\n| Item | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| Main .env files permissions (600) | ✅ Correct |\n| Credentials directory (700) | ✅ Correct |\n| SSH private key (600) | ✅ Correct |\n| Gateway binds to localhost only | ✅ Secure |\n| Dashboard binds to localhost only | ✅ Secure |\n| Gateway token authentication enabled | ✅ Secure |\n| Telegram allowFrom restrictions | ✅ Secure |\n| Dashboard secret redaction active | ✅ Secure |\n| No credentials in git history | ✅ Clean |\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Network Security Status\n\n| Service | Port | Bind Address | Status |\n|---------|------|--------------|--------|\n| OpenClaw Gateway | 18789 | 127.0.0.1 | ✅ Secure |\n| Dashboard | 8789 | 127.0.0.1 | ✅ Secure |\n| Node Service | 8888 | 127.0.0.1 | ✅ Secure |\n| AI Tunnel | 8081 | 0.0.0.0 | ⚠️ **EXPOSED** |\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 PRIORITY FIXES\n\n### Immediate (Today)\n```bash\n# 1. Fix world-readable credential file\nchmod 600 /home/darwin/.openclaw/ARCHIVED/aiopsflow-nextjs-full/.env.local\n\n# 2. Consider rotating exposed tokens\n# - Supabase anon key (if sensitive operations use it)\n# - Telegram bot token: 8652287514:AAGPP4zXkJR--NPo4nsTMZobqBJZ_prtqf8\n```\n\n### High Priority (This Week)\n```bash\n# 3. Fix tunnel server to bind localhost only\n# Edit: /home/darwin/.openclaw/workspace/ai-gateway/tunnel-server/ai_handler.py\n# Change bind from \"0.0.0.0\" to \"127.0.0.1\"\n\n# 4. Move GitHub Copilot token to env variable\n# Update auth-profiles.json to use env reference instead of plain token\n```\n\n### Medium Priority (This Month)\n1. Review all backup files for credential exposure\n2. Add automated credential scanning to CI/CD\n3. Implement secret rotation policy\n4. Document secure credential recovery procedures\n\n---\n\n## 📈 RECOMMENDATIONS\n\n1. **Use a secrets manager** (e.g., HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager)\n2. **Implement pre-commit hooks** to prevent credential commits\n3. **Regular security audits** (quarterly)\n4. **Enable 2FA** on all service accounts (Telegram, GitHub, etc.)\n5. **Monitor for credential leaks** using GitHub secret scanning\n6. **Document incident response plan** for credential compromise\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 BOTTOM LINE\n\n**Good news**: Core OpenClaw infrastructure is properly secured with correct file permissions and localhost-only bindings.\n\n**Bad news**: The ARCHIVED folder contains a world-readable .env file with live credentials, and the Python tunnel server is exposed to all network interfaces. These are exploitable vulnerabilities.\n\n**Action required**: Fix the world-readable credential file and tunnel server binding immediately."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":499,"output":1490,"cacheRead":27904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalToken